module.purpose:
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of wires and cables in a design context together with the terminals on them so that they can be connected in an assembly. This application module supports the representation of cables consisting of wires, without the need to establish formal assembly structures. The focus is on the conductors of cables and wires that are isolated from each other and on the terminals to connect to the conductors. The construction details of a wire or cable such as insulation and jacket are not needed for this representation.
the conductors in wires and cables are treated as electrical transport features;
typically cables and wires are purchased as raw material material. A particular occurrence of a cable or wire for an electrical design is produced from the raw materials by cutting to a specific length;
color based identification codes can be used to identify individual wires in a cable;
wires and cables are contacted by terminals that are either on one of the ends or at intermediate locations;
the terminals on the wires of a cable are grouped by their location at either one of the cable ends or an intermediate location;
cable and wire occurrence may receive an alphanumeric or bar-code mark for identification purpose.
